dataIdInfo.idAbs: Approximate areas covered by each US Postal Service (USPS) Zip Code in San Diego County. Areas are approximate boundaries only as determined by SanGIS and SanGIS JPA member users and associates. Does not represent an official depiction of USPS Zip Code boundaries. Does not represent all zip codes that may be used in the County. Certain Zip Codes are assigned for post office boxes only and cannot be represented by polygons. Note that the USPS does not define a Zip Code as an area. USPS defines a zip code as the identifier for the post office that mail will be delivered from. SanGIS Zip Code boundaries are approximated from situs addresses and information received from SanGIS JPA members and associates.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Approximate outline of area served for each US Postal Service Zip Code in San Diego County.

overview.eaover: This dataset is keyed on the five digit Zip Code value assigned by the US Postal Service and provides the common name of the post office associated with that Zip Code. Typically all zip codes in an incorporated city will have the same name as that of the municipality (e.g. Carlsbad). One exception is that La Jolla has its own post office name even though it is within the City of San Diego. Post offices in unincorporated areas will the common community name. Post office assigned to Zip Codes are determined by the US Postal Service.
